# Aplica Components — Implementation Guide

## Before writing code
1. Read `dist/css/<brand>-light.css` — exact CSS variable names for this workspace. Never invent them.
2. Check `aplica-theme-engine.config.mjs` for `surfacePolarity` — if `'positive'`, negative surface tokens don't exist.

## Token contract (per state)
Every function/feedback state generates: `background`, `border`, `txtOn` (text on bg), `txt` (standalone text, if enabled).
Use `txtOn` for text placed on a colored background.

## Key patterns
- **Button states**: `..normal.bg` → `..action.bg` (hover) → `..active.bg` (pressed) + `disabled` uses opacity token
- **Ghost variant**: text color from `ghostNormalTxtOnStrategy` config — `'txt'` = body, `'surface'` = page bg
- **Feedback**: `feedback.success.default.*` (filled) vs `feedback.success.secondary.*` (subtle)
- **Typography**: use generated composite styles — never decompose font/size/weight/line-height manually
- **Elevation**: use generated shadow tokens — never write raw `box-shadow` values

## Dark mode
Apply dark class to root element. Load both `dist/css/<brand>-light.css` and `dist/css/<brand>-dark.css`.
Check dark CSS file for exact selector (`.dark`, `.theme-dark`, etc.).

## Portal pattern (Base UI, Radix, Floating UI)
Apply theme class to `document.body`, not just app root. Portals render outside component tree and lose CSS scope.
Dark class stays on `document.documentElement`; theme class on `document.body`.

## Archetypes
Button, Input/Select, Dialog/Modal, Badge, Card, Tabs, Tooltip.
Dialogs and Tooltips require portal pattern if using headless libraries.

## Hard rules
- Never hardcode `px`, `hex`, `rgba()`, raw shadows, or radii.
- Never invent variable names — derive from `dist/css/` only.
- Never assume `negative` surface exists without checking config.

